[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi,<br>\nBack in December I started playing around with building out-of-tree Rust modules for the ArchLinux kernel: <a href=\"https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module.html\">https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module.html</a>. This lead to me creating my custom build of the ArchLinux kernel (<a href=\"https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module-part-two.html\">https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module-part-two.html</a>) to actually have Rust support and later compiling it in a way and package the metadata that it actually works to build out-of-tree Rust modules without having the kernel build tree locally: <a href=\"https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module-part-three.html\">https://blog.rnstlr.ch/building-an-out-of-tree-rust-kernel-module-part-three.html</a></p>\n<p>Now I wanted to update my custom kernel from 6.2 to 6.3 and get now again errors while trying to build the out-of-tree module:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">main</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">%</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">KDIR</span><span class=\"o\">=/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">modules</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"mf\">6.3.8</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">arch1</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">build</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">C</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">modules</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"mf\">6.3.8</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">arch1</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">build</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"cp\">$PWD</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"n\">projects</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">github</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust_out_of_tree</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">could</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_out_of_tree</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rust_out_of_tree</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ad9c6f77</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">cgu</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mf\">0.</span><span class=\"n\">rcgu</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Permission</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">denied</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">aborting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">due</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">previous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">scripts</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">build</span>:<span class=\"mi\">304</span>: <span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"n\">projects</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">github</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust_out_of_tree</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">2025</span>: <span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"n\">projects</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">github</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">Linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">rust</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">out</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">of</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">tree</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n<span class=\"n\">make</span>: <span class=\"o\">***</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>:<span class=\"mi\">6</span>: <span class=\"nc\">default</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Error</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Does anyone have a pointer what the issue could be? I guess the build process tries to output a file into the <code>/lib/modules/...</code> folder somewhere?</p>",
        "id": 367742473,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1687205633
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Difficult to tell from the output, but it looks like your don't have write permissions to the local directory where you are building. When you build like this, the build system should not write to any folder outside of the build directory.</p>",
        "id": 367822476,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1687245131
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">could</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">write</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">output</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rust_out_of_tree</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rust_out_of_tree</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">ad9c6f77</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">cgu</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"mf\">0.</span><span class=\"n\">rcgu</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>: <span class=\"nc\">Permission</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">denied</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">error</span>: <span class=\"nc\">aborting</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">due</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">previous</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">error</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>looks like that your object file have different permission? maybe you run a <code>sudo make install</code>? <code>sudo make clean</code> should delete it i guess</p>",
        "id": 367845359,
        "sender_full_name": "Vincenzo Palazzo",
        "timestamp": 1687250522
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The issue is that <code>rustc</code> creates temporary files in the current working directory by default (even if <code>--emit</code> is passed, i.e. it does not use those paths for the temporary files, so I think we need to control the temporary files via <code>--out-dir</code>).</p>",
        "id": 367856811,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687252939
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(and the CWD is not the right place in the out-of-tree case)</p>",
        "id": 367856864,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687252958
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Filed <a href=\"https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/1015\">https://github.com/Rust-for-Linux/linux/issues/1015</a></p>",
        "id": 367856883,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687252963
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Could you please try this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Diff\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"gh\">diff --git a/scripts/Makefile.build b/scripts/Makefile.build</span>\n<span class=\"gh\">index 94d67252df4e..261e51c0af59 100644</span>\n<span class=\"gd\">--- a/scripts/Makefile.build</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+++ b/scripts/Makefile.build</span>\n<span class=\"gu\">@@ -287,7 +287,7 @@ rust_common_cmd = \\</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>       --extern alloc --extern kernel \\\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>       --crate-type rlib -L $(objtree)/rust/ \\\n<span class=\"w\"> </span>       --crate-name $(basename $(notdir $@)) \\\n<span class=\"gd\">-       --emit=dep-info=$(depfile)</span>\n<span class=\"gi\">+       --out-dir $(dir $@) --emit=dep-info=$(depfile)</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\"> </span># `--emit=obj`, `--emit=asm` and `--emit=llvm-ir` imply a single codegen unit\n<span class=\"w\"> </span># will be used. We explicitly request `-Ccodegen-units=1` in any case, and\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 367856986,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687252988
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"583152\">@Raphael Nestler</span> If that works for you, do you mind appearing in a commit message with a <code>Reported-by</code> tag with your name and email? Also, if you test it and it works for you, a <code>Tested-by</code> tag would be great, too. Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 367857960,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687253227
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"411477\">@Miguel Ojeda</span> I will test it right away and I'm OK with <code>Reported-by</code> and <code>Tested-by</code> tag.</p>",
        "id": 367865116,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1687254801
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It doesn't seem to work. I patched the file directly in <code>/usr/lib/modules/6.3.8-arch1-1/build/scripts/Makefile.build</code> though. Also I don't see the <code>--out-dir</code> flag appearing anywhere when I grep the output of <code>make KDIR=/lib/modules/6.3.8-arch1-1-rust/build LLVM=1 -n</code></p>",
        "id": 367869183,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1687255613
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>From what I can tell, you are changing the working directory to the path starting with <code>/lib</code>, not <code>/usr/lib</code>.</p>",
        "id": 367871562,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687256123
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you have two kernel sources, one in <code>/usr/lib</code> and one in <code>/lib</code>?</p>",
        "id": 367871635,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687256146
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i.e. if you have both <code>/usr/lib/modules/6.3.8-arch1-1/build/scripts/Makefile.build</code> and <code>/lib/modules/6.3.8-arch1-1/build/scripts/Makefile.build</code>, from the commands above (with <code>KDIR=/lib/...</code>or <code>-C /lib/...</code>), the one that would be actually used is the latter.</p>",
        "id": 367872643,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687256361
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Thanks a lot for testing it, by the way!)</p>",
        "id": 367875001,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1687256862
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ArchLinux has <code>/lib</code> merged into <code>/usr/lib</code>, meaning that <code>/lib</code> is just a symlink to <code>/usr/lib</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">%</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ls</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">lh</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span>\n<span class=\"n\">lrwxrwxrwx</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">root</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">7</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mf\">31.</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Jan</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">21</span>:<span class=\"mi\">51</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span><span class=\"w\"> </span>-&gt; <span class=\"nc\">usr</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">lib</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 368277606,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1687361241
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But sorry for the confusion, I should just have used the same paths to avoid confusion.</p>",
        "id": 368278071,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1687361317
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I tested today and it seems to work. I'm not sure what I did wrong last week.</p>",
        "id": 370041659,
        "sender_full_name": "Raphael Nestler",
        "timestamp": 1687868512
    }
]